osAgent is NOT ZeroClaw
================================================================================

osAgent is an independent fork. We do not represent ZeroClaw Labs and we do not
claim affiliation with the ZeroClaw project, its trademark, or its branding.
For the official upstream ZeroClaw distribution, see:

  https://github.com/zeroclaw-labs/zeroclaw

osAgent diverges from upstream in material ways:
  - Two compile-time-separated binaries (`engineer`, `wizard`) replacing one daemon
  - The `wizard` binary has zero MCP capability, enforced at the crate-dependency layer
  - ~26 chat/social channels, ~50 LLM providers, ~35 tools, and the hardware/robotics/
    desktop crates are stripped at the source level
  - A native AMQP-mTLS bridge tool, file-exchange channel, lifecycle gates, and a
    customer-keyed sqlcipher memory layer are added

If you need ZeroClaw, get ZeroClaw. If you need osAgent's particular shape, you
are in the right place.

